Use pg_hba.conf to Temporarily Disable Password Requirement
1. Edit pg_hba.conf
 -> Windows: C:\Program Files\PostgreSQL\<version>\data\pg_hba.conf
  
   	Find the line like:
	local   all             all                                     md5
	
	Change md5 â†’ trust:
	local   all             all                                     trust
	
2. Restart PostgreSQL
  -> sudo systemctl restart postgresql
  
3. Connect without password
 -> psql -U postgres

4. Reset password
 -> ALTER USER postgres WITH PASSWORD 'NewPassword123!';
 

5. Restore security
 -> Change trust back to md5 and restart PostgreSQL again.